# Documentation Standards

- When behavior changes, update the closest canonical docs (for example `README.md` or `source/*.md`) in the same change.
- Keep examples runnable and aligned with current API names and arguments.
- Prefer concise sections with concrete commands or snippets over long prose.
- Clearly call out compatibility notes or breaking changes.
- For TTSL updates, ensure opcode/assembly semantics stay synchronized with docs.
- For Sphinx `.rst` pages: **one document title** underlined with `=` only; demote every other heading (`-`, `^`, …). Never repeat the top-level adornment within the same page.
